    <p><strong>Using the given table, complete the following steps:</strong></p>

    <ol>
      <li>
        <strong>a) Sort the data by the Salesperson column in ascending (Aâ€“Z) order using the Custom Sort feature and Select the entire data table and apply All Borders, then apply a Thick Outside Border to outline the table clearly.</strong>
      </li>

      <li>
        <strong>b) Apply the following Number Formatting to the specified columns:</strong>
        <ul>
          <li>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Total Revenue:</strong> Currency</li>
          <li>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Units Sold:</strong> Number</li>
          <li>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Order Date:</strong> Short Date</li>
          <li>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Transaction Time:</strong> Time</li>
          <li>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Discount Rate:</strong> Percentage (with 1 decimal place)</li>
        </ul>
      </li>

      <li>
        <strong>c) Create a chart to compare the Total Revenue for each Product Category, and complete the following within the chart:</strong>
        <ol type="1">
          <li>Identify and indicate the Product Category with the highest Total Revenue.</li>
          <li>Add a clear title to the chart.</li>
          <li>Label the X-axis and Y-axis appropriately.</li>
          <li>Apply a pre-set Chart Style of your choice for better visual presentation.</li>
        </ol>
      </li>
    </ol>
